  "text": "In Drosophila the homologue of Hec1/Cdh, Fzr, also induces the APC/Ccomplex-dependent proteolysis of CycA and B and is required for the G1-phase progression [CITATION_1] . Fzr is required for cyclin removal during G1 when the embryonic epidermal cell or follicle epithelial proliferation stops and the cells enter endocycles [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
